<DOC><DOCNO> AP890428-0232 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-28-89 1244EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f PM-RJRNabisco     04-28 0298</FIRST><SECOND>PM-RJR Nabisco,0308</SECOND><HEAD>Kohlberg Completes RJR Nabisco Buyout</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The maverick buyout firm Kohlberg Kravis Robertsandamp; Co. said today it has completed its record $24.53 billionacquisition of RJR Nabisco Inc.   Trading in the company's stock on the New York Stock Exchangewas to cease at the end of the day.   The completion of the deal that stunned Wall Street came a dayafter shareholders formally approved the buyout at a specialmeeting in Wilmington, Del. Company officials said about 85 percentof RJR Nabisco's shares were voted in favor of the merger.   Separately, RJR Nabisco announced Thursday that it would moveits headquarters from Atlanta to the New York City area by the endof the year so the food-and-tobacco giant can be in close contactwith the financial community.   The company will decide over the next few weeks whether layoffsare necessary, said Pauline Howes, an RJR Nabisco spokeswoman.About 450 RJR Nabisco employees work in Atlanta, she said.   The move would be the second for RJR Nabisco corporateheadquarters in recent years. Former RJR President F. Ross Johnsonmoved the headquarters from Winston-Salem to Atlanta after he tookover following the merger of R.J. Reynolds Industries Inc. andNabisco Brands Inc. in 1985.   RJR Nabisco said its new chairman, Louis Gerstner Jr., sent aletter to employees saying the plans of the firm can ``best beachieved by maintaining close ongoing contact with the investmentbanking community and other New York-based segments of the businesscommunity.''   The letter said relocations could begin by early summer andwould be completed by the end of the year.   The exact location of RJR Nabisco's headquarters was notannounced. However, the firm's Nabisco Brands division is based inNew Jersey, also near New York.</TEXT></DOC>